===============================================================================
WHY EVERY ADDITIONAL ELEMENT WAS ADDED
===============================================================================

1. SECOND LOAD BALANCER (HAProxy Cluster):

- Why: To eliminate the Load Balancer as a Single Point of Failure (SPOF).
- How it works: The two HAProxy instances are configured as a cluster in an
  ACTIVE-PASSIVE setup using a Virtual IP (VRRP/Keepalived). If the Active
  Load Balancer crashes, the Passive one instantly takes over (Failover),
  ensuring zero downtime for users.

2. SPLITTING THE COMPONENTS ONTO DEDICATED SERVERS:

- Why: To stop resource competition and optimize performance.
- In the previous tasks, Nginx, the Application Server, and MySQL shared the
  same CPU and RAM, causing bottlenecks. By giving each component its own
  isolated server, they can run at maximum efficiency and be scaled up
  independently.

3. ADDITIONAL SERVER (Scaling Out):

- Why: To handle more traffic (increasing QPS) and provide redundancy at
  every layer of the web stack.

===============================================================================
THE COMPLETE ARCHITECTURE LAYERS (HOW IT FLOWS)
===============================================================================

- LAYER 1: HIGH AVAILABILITY LOAD BALANCING
  The user request hits the High Availability HAProxy Cluster (Active-Passive).
  The active HAProxy routes the traffic to the Web layer.

- LAYER 2: DEDICATED WEB SERVERS (Nginx)
  The request lands on a dedicated Web Server running Nginx. Its ONLY job
  is to handle incoming HTTP/HTTPS traffic, serve static assets, and proxy
  dynamic requests to the next layer.

- LAYER 3: DEDICATED APPLICATION SERVERS
  The dedicated Application Server receives the request from Nginx. Its ONLY
  job is to execute the codebase files and generate dynamic content.

- LAYER 4: DEDICATED DATABASE CLUSTER (MySQL)
  The Application Server connects to the isolated MySQL Database Cluster.
  Writes go to the Primary node, and Reads go to the Replica node.

===============================================================================
CONCLUSION: NO MORE SPOF
===============================================================================
Thanks to this infrastructure design, if any single server catches fire or
crashes (a web server, an app server, or a load balancer), another one is
always ready to handle the traffic. The architecture is now fully redundant,
secure, and scalable.
